---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const effectiveDate = new Intl.DateTimeFormat("en-US", {
  dateStyle: "long",
  timeZone: "UTC",
}).format(new Date("2026-07-21T00:00:00Z"));
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description="How BES3 handles the limited information connected with a visit to the site."
>
  <section class="page-hero shell">
    <div><p class="eyebrow">LEGAL</p><h1>Privacy, in plain language.</h1></div><p class="lede">
      BES3 is designed to be read without creating an account or sharing personal information.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="section reading-width article-body">
    <p><strong>Effective date: <time datetime="2026-07-21">{effectiveDate}</time></strong></p>
    <h2>Information we collect</h2><p>
      BES3 does not offer user accounts, comments, a newsletter sign-up or a contact form. You can
      browse the site without directly providing us with your name, email address or payment
      information.
    </p>
    <h2>Hosting and essential technical data</h2><p>
      BES3 is delivered through Cloudflare Pages. Like most web hosts, Cloudflare may process
      limited technical information, such as an IP address, browser details and request data, to
      deliver and protect the site. BES3 does not add advertising, marketing or analytics cookies to
      its pages. Cloudflare's handling of information is described in its{" "}
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>
    <h2>Email you choose to send</h2><p>
      If you email the editorial desk, we receive the information included in your message and use
      it only to review, respond to or follow up on your request. Keep sensitive health or personal
      information out of email where possible.
    </p>
    <h2>Links to other sites</h2><p>
      Articles may link to manufacturers, retailers, research sources and other third-party sites.
      Those sites have their own privacy practices. Once you leave BES3, review the privacy notice
      of the destination you visit.
    </p>
    <h2>Commercial links</h2><p>
      Some links may be affiliate links, meaning BES3 may earn a commission if a purchase is made.
      This does not change the price for you or the way we make editorial decisions. Read our
      {" "}<a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a> for details.
    </p>
    <h2>Your choices</h2><p>
      To ask about or request deletion of information you have sent to us by email, contact the
      editorial desk. We will review the request in line with applicable law and our need to retain
      correspondence for legitimate editorial or legal purposes.
    </p>
    <h2>Changes to this notice</h2><p>
      If our information practices change, we will update this page and its effective date before
      applying the new practice.
    </p>
    <h2>Contact</h2><p>
      Privacy questions can be sent to <a href="mailto:editorial@bes3.com">editorial@bes3.com</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
